TextBlock.TextLine: C 25 apld 1683
Thaunton mr. Thomas Ledgingham
Ihough this long sence, that I have hatch non from you, occasioned because the last
goods die not prove to exspectation, yett am resolved to make an other try all, where
fore desire you to gett made for mee, 12 blewlists white perpetuanees, of 1½ youd full
broad, & no lest then 24 yd long, pure good, & heary goods, ray lett them be made to
purpose & I'll racher come to the price, & allow some p. more then formerly, for then
could not serve my turne, & must have vere good, Inbstantial goods, I will not his
you the payce nor time, so desire to have them wish all these qualikes menroned
which tryall in case proves well will cause many to be ordered, so once againe le
mee intreat you to assrs mee there in, & you will oblige mee, & I'ill see you
duely satissied, they an to be made up in one bale, & to be shipped of att
on Thopsam, pray a word of answer
C 25d
Londen m. Henry Maynard
mij last to you was on the 27 cor. sence non from you. Bon: clarck & Baulatso
are well arriveed, for which sod be thancked, butt reae nothing yett Pindar
I hope the G.W. slver marchs are ships, for I am vere much prested fortle
same, besides the pack whites Insended by the same desire you an oth pack
to be bought of 5 of each sort, wish 5 of a lower rate as desined in my som
I exspect the reds shipt as also yd advise how woll will iule there is
report here, that spaim will prohibitt the sending of woll to ings, as also all
English manifacturijes in any of dis domimons, oneles the king of Eugland wild
declare against france, so that itt is all upon ware againe. in the meane while
please to send yd. oader in the north to make 50 white kerties of 1½ lenght
all red iys and about a geard broad, of a good woll, made to the purpose as
thick as the 22 yd, them to be dispatched, att least ½ the quantitie to come wich smcl
there by one bale to containe do white tertyes 22 yd and 20 of 30 yd all good
goods, for the best sell best also one bale to containe to red kerties 22 yd
and 10 red kersies 30 yd. every bale to be wrapped with 3 or 4 white manchester
bayes of 40 p & more ordres prept with remises accordingly. now come to a
sorry news that John vale is broake, & I doubt he will not srove so henese as
wogelen thoughe hyn be which partely you will see
the inclosed notes which I tought god to send you witt tre or iudge by the
inclosed notes, which I thought good to send you, to yd god &
Londen mr. Edmund Waner
mij last to you was on the 18 curtt. sence non from you, the packett n 22 went
from Gence butt y casterday, inclosed the invoyce of ns 23 which goedh forward
a minday nept, for the valew please to give mee credit, to n°423 is of the goods
boughs for marly & of the good cheap the rest, & what elce I shall send is at prce
curtt, for never in this world was haces demanded as now itt is to yd sord
indeed I am not able to accomplish orders as I could desire, wholver be confident
that I take as much care as pou can be smagined, to promote yd. Intrest by the
inclosed note of the stelen goods you will finde 3 p of laces more them by the
formar acut sent, which sence recovered, I have ne ma to inlarge
the most part for n. 24 is ready
London mr. Heny Collusr
mij last to you was on the p curtt sence non from you, this to my great gref for advise
that John vale is broake & by the inclosed note you will be able touidge, that itt
is much seared, that he will prove a great krave, I have given the needfull oarden fo
bieuring you, yett I can not go shearkes before midle of nept wick, I mett wish m
of yd bills protested butt one of £20- s for Pickerings, which I have payd, you
must send over yd. som, or come yd self, as well for this as for T.H., whois this
weck exciuted, by sentence, & yett nour hew one pemue to be iccovaed, so
Iam mucl concerned to see you thus afsleted in every side, whilst I could
wish itt other wil
